<p>High-tannin reds like Cabernet Sauvignon clash with salmon's delicate proteins, creating metallic, bitter flavors. Similarly, heavily oaked Chardonnays can overwhelm subtle preparations, while very light wines like basic Pinot Grigio lack the structure to complement richer salmon dishes.</p>

